Our middle school “farm club” will be running a mini robot event where alliances of three v three will play FRC style to push assorted amusing objects into variable sized scoring baskets. Blue and Red of course. Is there an easy way to generate pairings? We expect nine entrants (seven of our middle school kids and two “staff” robots). Probably four or five rounds of quals then, much easier, a best of three between the two finalist alliances. Should be easy-peasy but how to generate these pairings?
